'''

Screen switching function

We need a function that picks which frame we need to show. Originally
I had the idea to build this into other functions, but I had many 
issues. After calling upon AI, I settled upon building a helper 
function whos entire purpose is to take an input 'frame_to_show'
which is the exact frame that we want to display at the moment and
do the following:

1) turn off all other frames

2) display 'frame_to_show'

The input should always be one of start_menu_frame, main_frame, 
or end_screen_frame.

This function is super useful and will end up being called in 
several other functions. 

'''
def show_frame(frame_to_show):
    # stop displaying all frames
    start_menu_frame.pack_forget()
    main_frame.pack_forget()
    end_screen_frame.pack_forget()
    #display the one frame we tell it to
    frame_to_show.pack()

'''

I needed a new tkinter compatible choos_difficulty fucntion. This is because of the 
way that tkinter loops work. My jupyter notebooks code worked via a loop that was
waiting for user input, but tkinter works with a main loop, which runs a function
when the user presses a button. So I need to make a new function which gets called
instantaeously rather than waiting for user input.

This function also updates current_state and lives in the main_frame,
then displays the main frame once the user has selected difficulty

'''

def choose_difficulty(difficulty):
   
   # establishing global variables so that we can change them in this function
   global secret_word, current_state, lives_used, letters_guessed

   # choosing the secret word using the previous function we made
   secret_word = word_picking_func(difficulty)

   # setting the current state to a string of underscores with the same length as 
   # the secret word
   current_state = ' '.join('_' * len(secret_word))

   # resetting lives used and letters guessed for the new round
   lives_used = 0
   letters_guessed = []

   # updating the current_state being displayed in the main game 
   reveal_label.config(text = current_state)
   lives_label.config(text = f'You have used {lives_used} / 8 lives')

   # using helper function to display the main game frame
   show_frame(main_frame)

#initialising the start menu as the first frame
show_frame(start_menu_frame)

